HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 326
BY REPRESENTATIVE JACOB LANDRY
A RESOLUTION
To commend Shani Sonnier for her service as the 2025-2026 Delcambre Shrimp Festival
Queen and to recognize her advocacy for Louisiana seafood, its shrimping industry,
Vermilion Parish, and the state of Louisiana.
WHEREAS, the Delcambre Shrimp Festival is held annually in the town of
Delcambre in both Iberia and Vermilion Parishes; the festival began as a fundraiser for the
local fire department and has grown into one of Louisiana's premier seafood festivals; and
WHEREAS, the Delcambre Shrimp Festival celebrates the shrimping industry and
Cajun culture through events such as shrimp cook-offs, live music, pageants, carnival rides,
boat parades, fais-do-dos, and the traditional Blessing of the Fleet honoring local fishermen;
and
WHEREAS, the shrimping industry has long played an essential role in the economy,
culture, and traditions of south Louisiana, and the Delcambre Shrimp Festival serves as a
meaningful tribute to the hardworking fishermen and seafood producers who sustain our
coastal communities across the state; and
WHEREAS, as Delcambre Shrimp Festival Queen, Shani Sonnier proudly represents
the festival and serves as an ambassador for Louisiana seafood and the shrimping industry
through her leadership, public service, and advocacy; and
WHEREAS, Shani Sonnier's commitment to promoting Louisiana seafood,
supporting shrimpers, and representing Vermilion Parish and the state of Louisiana has
brought great pride to the Delcambre Shrimp Festival and the communities she serves; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting to commend Shani Sonnier for promoting Louisiana's
seafood heritage and recognize her service as the 2025-2026 Delcambre Shrimp Festival
Queen.
